# HTML Standards for Webundance

## Document Structure
- Use HTML5 semantic elements: header, nav, main, section, article, aside, footer
- Include proper meta tags in this order:
  1. charset
  2. viewport
  3. title
  4. description
  5. Open Graph tags
  6. favicon links

## SEO Requirements
- One H1 per page containing primary keyword
- Proper heading hierarchy (never skip levels)
- Alt text on all images (descriptive, includes keywords naturally)
- Title tags: 50-60 characters
- Meta descriptions: 150-160 characters

## Component Structure Example:
```html
<article class="card service-card">
  <div class="card-icon">
    <img src="/images/icon.svg" alt="Description" width="60" height="60" loading="lazy">
  </div>
  <h3 class="card-title">Title</h3>
  <p class="card-description">Description text</p>
  <a href="/page" class="btn btn-primary">
    Learn More
    <span class="sr-only">additional context for screen readers</span>
  </a>
</article>

## Accessibility

Use semantic HTML before ARIA
Include skip navigation link
Form labels properly associated
Buttons for actions, links for navigation
Focus indicators on all interactive elements
